{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"agent_message","text":"The current `epiphyseal tract` stanza exactly matches the problematic axiom from the issue. For `adductor muscle of hip`, the term has no definition but does carry cross-references to mammalian/human sources and a tetrapod-specific `innervated_by` axiom, so I’m checking descendants and related imported mappings before choosing the smaller ontology change."}}
